  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A binding requirement mandates experimental-validation as the required verification method for hemolysis predictions; however, the supporting validation result was generated by a high-fidelity numerical simulation activity, which the assessment narrative argues is functionally equivalent to a physical experiment given the parametric sweep coverage. The structured activity record nonetheless records activityType as numerical-simulation, creating an inference-method mismatch that undercuts the verification chain.",
